-- TSB says will relocate some operations if Scots vote "yes"
-- By Matt Scuffham
-- Thu Sep 11, 2014 06:21AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 11 (Reuters) - TSB Banking Group <TSB.L> has become the fourth bank to say it is likely to relocate some operations to England should Scotland vote for independence.

TSB's announcement follows Royal Bank of Scotland <RBS.L>,  Lloyds Banking Group <LLOY.L> and National Australia Bank's Clydesdale <NAB.AX> which have said they will re-locate. [ID:nL5N0RB5S2]